The Rand West municipality in Gauteng is expected to cough up R3-million before the 30th of June to fix its environmental mess up. The municipality is said to have polluted some rivers in the area through sewage spillage and partially untreated wastewater. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There's a hefty fine for contravening the National Environmental Act. The Rand West municipality in Gauteng has pleaded guilty to this and has been slapped with a R10-million fine. Only R3-million of this is payable. The municipality discharged partially untreated water into a river threatening the lives of communities. Complainants hope this court victory will be a first step to holding municipalities responsible for their negligence. * eNCA's Nqobile Madlala reports.